  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      &quot;God always has <font face="Gulim, sans-serif"><span lang="zxx">&#54620;</span></font>(<i>han </i><span style="font-style: normal">sorrow</span>, regret, or resentment) that He couldn't be the Father who could console and have the environmental factors that allows Him to encourage me. I can always almost see my blooming time of energy and hope when I urged myself to go to and be with Heavenly Father sacrificing everything of that time. Only those who experienced it can understand the earnestness of such heart. You should have such mind. In the valley of repentance, holding sorrowful situations with agonizing face where parents can have no sympathy, shedding tears of sadness rather than that of joy meant to me that it was the time of eternal farewell. I could hear the sound of weeping from the bones at the time. Who can know the situation of my youth, where I had to take the difficult path even knowing there was an easy path to go. That was an earnest heart. Even I am over 90 and reaching 100, I will never forget such heart. In such a world of heart, heavenly grace will gradually become bigger and bigger. You should have such a world in your life.&quot;
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
