<node TEXT="When did the four rules of start to be used?" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_558567178" CREATED="1433320777497" MODIFIED="1433320782317">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<node TEXT="18 Jan 2011&#xa;&#xa;" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" ID="ID_150791388" CREATED="1435280390504" MODIFIED="1437604002024" LINK="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-110118.htm">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<richcontent TYPE="DETAILS">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      When did the four rules of arithmetic (addition, subtraction, multiplication and division) start to be used? Was it before or after the human fall? Nobody has thought of it. Addition and multiplication are like friends with each other, and they cannot be separated. Subtraction and division seem similar but they dislike each other. 1 + 1 = 2 but 1 - 1 = 0 and so nothing remains. 1 + 3 = 4 but if 3 is divided by 4, (the number 3) is gone. How come such mathematics was created? There are single numbers, and then comes the number 10. From there it must go to 11 but how can it do so? Everything has its reciprocal partner, and the physics and geometry which do not have such a concept have been fundamentally mistaken.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120116.htm">http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120116.htm </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      9x9=81 is from fallen man, it should be 102
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120111.htm">http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120111.htm</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;Why does 9 x 9 make 81, not 102, being reduced by 21? (Raising his voice) Who made this? The history of the fall made this.&quot;
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="In God, everything must get bigger" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_463950783" CREATED="1433320782583" MODIFIED="1433325282230">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<node TEXT="22 Feb 2011&#xa;&#xa;" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" ID="ID_842771079" CREATED="1435280490416" MODIFIED="1435280587660" LINK="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-110222.htm">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<richcontent TYPE="DETAILS">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      &quot;The four rules of arithmetic (addition, subtraction, multiplication and division) don't exist in God. In God everything must get bigger and bigger. 9 x 9 is 81 but it should be 91 or 102. Without solving this problem, there will be no world of peace. This is a serious problem.&quot;
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-110928.htm">http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-110928.htm </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;Why does 9 x 9 make 81? It should be 91 or 102 while reproducing sons and daughters and dominate the whole cosmos.&quot;
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-111127.htm">http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-111127.htm </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      4 x 8 makes 32, which is the number of our teeth
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
