    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;There is a formula and if you know it you do not have to worry: Satan will escape from you. I said (Katsumi: it is in North Korean dialect, which means something which does not exist but seems to exist. But it seems Father uses the term indicating something that exists spiritually). When you pass a crossroad which is connected to east, west, north and south, it will ask you without fail from where you come from, north, south, east or west. If you do not answer, it will immediately give you pain by kicking you. It thinks 'Why didn't you answer, even when you know the answer!' When it helps you heal but you do not follow, it will not help you again. When you become sick, you cannot heal yourself alone. You need to find a motive with which you can be united with heaven and earth, and have to know where you reside for the harvest.&quot;
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;Those who pray a lot say 'vertical and horizontal' not 'horizontal and vertical.' 'Vertical' comes first.&quot;
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
