<node TEXT="Bek rok Dam, Jeju island" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_602669491" CREATED="1433327225882" MODIFIED="1444771949485">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<node TEXT="01 Jul 2011&#xa;&#xa;" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" ID="ID_839759810" CREATED="1435727741714" MODIFIED="1444771907306" LINK="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon11/SunMyungMoon-110701.htm">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<richcontent TYPE="DETAILS">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      There is Bek Rok Dam (a pond on the top of Hal la mountain in Jejudo). You cannot find in any other place the relationship of husband and wife that the mountain symbolizes. 40 years ago I bought Jiguido (Jigui island, small island close to Jejudo) since I felt I had to buy it. When you see Halla mountain from the island, it looks like a Queen who died and lay herself down.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120421.htm">http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120421.htm </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120421.htm">
</a>    </p>
    <p>
      &quot;Mt. Halla in Jeju island is in the position of the wife of Mt. Baekdu in North Korea. There is Bek Rok Dam (a crater lake) on Mt. Halla. 40 years ago I bought Jiguido (a small island close to Jejudo) and wanted to educate people there but I couldn't.&quot;
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
