<node TEXT="06 Apr 2012&#xa;&#xa;" COLOR="#000000" STYLE="as_parent" MAX_WIDTH="600" MIN_WIDTH="1" ID="ID_1022628689" CREATED="1440493841009" MODIFIED="1440493899698" LINK="http://www.tparents.org/Moon-Talks/SunMyungMoon12/SunMyungMoon-120406.htm">
<edge STYLE="bezier" COLOR="#00ff00" WIDTH="thin"/>
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="10" BOLD="false" ITALIC="false"/>
<richcontent TYPE="DETAILS">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      How many islands does Japan consist of? ('There are four major islands.') Three thousand years ago, was there the name Hokkaido (<font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#21271;&#28023;&#36947;</span></font>) (which is one of the four)? ('There wasn't')
    </p>
    <p style="margin-left: 0.79in">
      (Katsumi: In Japan administratively there are 43 provinces and the Chinese character for 'province' is <font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#30476;</span></font>/ Ken. Then there are three other regions in Japan: Tokyo, Kyoto and Hokkaido. Tokyo is called Tokyoto with <font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#37117;</span></font>, Kyoto is called Kyotowho with <font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#24220;</span></font>, and Hokkaido with <font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#36947;</span></font>. In Korea the world 'province' is <font face="MS Gothic"><span lang="zxx">&#36947;</span></font>/ do, and therefore, what Father implied here is that <b>the area of Hokkaido had belonged to Korea</b>.)
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
